<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Every</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> spell-effect used by a Bard is treated as a Song regardless of how it was generated : Bard actually 'casting' the song, a proc, or a right-click of some sort.<br>
<br>
Songs can not require reagents without a serious reworking of the bard code.<br>
<br>
Therefore, Bards do not need the Quintesence.<br>
<br>
Fixing this would be almost guaranteed to break Bards yet again. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:medium;">Zyphyr Runnersbane</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
